Subject: Re: [T2] Re: [VB] Suggestions for tracking battery drain?

On 8/26/04 4:49 AM, "Dave Dixon" <ddixon(-at-)mbay.net> wrote:

> How about attaching a digital voltmeter to it while looking for the short
> that drains it? When the drain is discovered, the battery will stop draining
> and the digital voltmeter stops decreasing in voltage?
> Dave
> 
> Anyone have any suggestions on methods for tracking a battery drain?

It's current drain and you have to put the multimeter into ammeter mode and
wire it in series with the battery. Most DMMs have a 10A limit so you have
to be careful with them even though they are often fused.

